We tried this relatively new (less than a year old I believe?) restaurant after we saw the awning from the street - total walk in. And wow. we stopped in for a drink and maybe an appetizer, we ended up trying 5 menu items and bringing home a pappardelle Bolognese. The scallops (on special) were amazing, the warm octopus cooked perfectly, Fried artichokes had just enough crispy breading inside and just enough warm cheese in the middle. Oysters, martinis, pear salad - great.  Now, on to the service. Gennaro was professional, jovial and honestly one of the more attentive yet not overly pressured servers I have had in a long time. He plated a serving from each of the specials, had good timing for table stops - real basic blocking and tackling that is easily overlooked but REALLY noticable when it's done right.  Not usually one for rave reviews but we'll be back to Baci. Frequently. Looking forward to it.

Having grown up in Italy, where our food was organically grown and unadulterated, I'm not easily impressed by Italian restaurants, so naturally, I was a bit skeptical when my husband told me he made reservations at a new Italian restaurant for our anniversary. However, Baci Ristorante quickly dispelled that skepticism. From the moment we entered and were cheerfully greeted by Natalie, my eyes feasted on the decor; it's modern, with radiant colors, but also infused with a Sicilian touch, you can feel the quality and creativity that went into it.  As we were seated, I noticed a bottle of wine at every table accompanied by lightly toasted bread and Caponatina (a traditional Sicilian appetizer).  Sal, the owner, brought out an antipasto that awakened my Italian palate. OMG! It consisted of two shrimps bowing to each other (a symbol of a couple), finely chopped almonds marinated in a party of flavors with an avocado cradling a crabmeat cocktail which was perfectly balanced with a balsamic reduction.  My main course was the Dover Sole, which Sal personally filleted for me right at our table. The fish was very fresh.  My husbands entree had an interesting twist: Gnocchi Alla Genovese; which consisted of gnocchi over a bed of San Marzano marinara sauce, then topped with a layer of pesto sauce capped with a creamy buratta in the center.  For dessert, we ordered the Vanilla Creme Brûlée which was pure perfection with an anniversary candle in the center, Sal also brought out a dish of warm Sicilian fig cookies, he, along with Mattia (one of the waiters), and the entire staff wished us a happy anniversary.  If you're looking for a clean, quality, healthy and delicious meal that leaves your stomach yearning for more... even after you're full... go to Baci!

Amazing addition to the neighborhood! Not one dish that we had tonight was below the excellent status. No complaints whatsoever. This place is definitely going to be a new go to restaurant and if you're ever in the area don't miss the opportunity to stop here! The space is beautiful and the food and service were excellent.  We were 3 people and shared all dishes.  We loved them all.  We started off with Octopus Baci, fried artichokes and the Baci salad. Then we moved on to pasta Anelletti al Forno which is a traditional Sicilian dish of ring shaped pasta in a meat and pea sauce baked with mozzarella. Absolutely delicious. For a main we shared the veal chop valdostano which was very large and perfect for sharing. It was a butterflies and pounded veal chop with prosciutto, fontina cheese in a mushroom Marsala sauce infused with black truffle and topped with wilted spinach.  That was equally delicious.  For dessert we had the bread pudding which was one of the best I have ever had.  An excellent experience.  I will be going back this week to try some other items on the menu.
